<subSubSection id="C30D654BFF26FF029A7FFC79FBEB34EC" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA836C0FF26FF029A7FFC79FBEB34EC" blockId="183.[151,1437,151,2014]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029A7FFC79F8E733A0" bold="true" box="[514,678,907,933]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">Polar Eelpout</emphasis>
or Canadian Eelpout. To a least 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FF26FF029C6DFC79FE2B33A0" box="[1040,1130,907,933]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3299999999999996" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" unit="cm" value="33.3">33.3 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FF26FF029C04FC79FE8933A3" box="[1145,1224,907,934]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3274" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" unit="in" value="13.1">13.1 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF26FF029D78FC79FB0633CC" author="Mecklenburg, C. W. &amp; Lynghammar, A. &amp; Johannesen, E. &amp; Byrkjedal, I. &amp; Christiansen, J. S. &amp; Dolgov, A. V. &amp; Karamushko, O. V. &amp; Mecklenburg, T. A. &amp; Moller, P. R. &amp; Steinke, D. &amp; Wienerrolther, R. M." pageId="183" pageNumber="184" refId="ref301135" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W., Lynghammar, A., Johannesen, E., Byrkjedal, I., Christiansen, J. S., Dolgov, A. V., Karamushko, O. V., Mecklenburg, T. A., Moller, P. R., Steinke, D. &amp; Wienerrolther, R. M. (2018) Marine Fishes of the Arctic Region. Conservation of Arctic Flora and Fauna, Akureyrl." type="book" year="2018">
Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF0298BBFC5DFB4033CC" box="[198,257,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). Nearly circumpolar; Beaufort and Chukchi Seas to eastern Bering Sea between Saint Matthew Island, and Saint Lawrence Island to western Bering Sea at Glubokaya Bay; as far north as 
<geoCoordinate id="EE235007FF26FF029CBAFC20FF6B33E8" box="[1223,1322,978,1005]" degrees="79" direction="north" minutes="55" orientation="latitude" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" precision="925" value="79.916664">79°55’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE235007FF26FF029D4BFC20FFDD33E8" box="[1334,1436,978,1005]" degrees="85" direction="west" minutes="20" orientation="longitude" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" precision="925" value="-85.333336">85°20’W</geoCoordinate>
in the high Canadian Arctic (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF26FF029A78FC05F95C3417" author="Mecklenburg, C. W. &amp; Mecklenburg, T. A. &amp; Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Steinke, D." box="[517,797,1015,1042]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" refId="ref301093" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W., Mecklenburg, T. A., Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Steinke, D. (2016) Pacific Arctic Marine Fishes. Conservation of Arctic Flora and Fauna, Akureyri." type="book" year="2016">
Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029ADFFC05F89B3414" box="[674,730,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Benthic; depth: 4 to more than 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FF26FF029CFAFC05FE8F3414" box="[1159,1230,1015,1041]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" unit="m" value="300.0">300 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FF26FF029CA1FC05FF0A3417" box="[1244,1355,1015,1042]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.519428" metricValueMax="2.999232" metricValueMin="0.039624" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" unit="ft" value="498.5" valueMax="984.0" valueMin="13.0">13–984 ft</quantity>
) (min.: Møller in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF26FF02994BFBE9F8743430" author="Coad, B. W. &amp; Reist, J. D." box="[310,565,1051,1077]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" refId="ref270835" refString="Coad, B. W. &amp; Reist, J. D. (Eds.). (2018) Marine Fishes of Arctic Canada. University of Toronto Press, Toronto." type="book" year="2018">Coad and Møller 2018</bibRefCitation>
; max.: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF26FF029AFAFBE9F9E53433" author="Mecklenburg, C. W. &amp; Mecklenburg, T. A. &amp; Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Steinke, D." box="[647,932,1051,1078]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" refId="ref301093" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W., Mecklenburg, T. A., Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Steinke, D. (2016) Pacific Arctic Marine Fishes. Conservation of Arctic Flora and Fauna, Akureyri." type="book" year="2016">
Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029B59FBE9F91F3430" box="[804,862,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). In the past, this species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FF26FF029CACFBE9FFD43431" authorityName="Richardson" authorityYear="1855" box="[1233,1429,1051,1077]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Lycodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mucosus">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029CACFBE9FFD43431" box="[1233,1429,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">Lycodes mucosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FF26FF02988BFBCDFBE6345D" authorityName="Bean" authorityYear="1879" box="[246,423,1087,1113]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Zoarcidae" genus="Lycodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="turneri">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF02988BFBCDFBE6345D" box="[246,423,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">Lycodes turneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were often been confused. The American Fisheries Society (Nelson 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029CD2FBCDFEA9345C" box="[1199,1256,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
2004) calls this fish the Canadian Eelpout, but its range is nearly circumpolar and Canadian (e.g., McAllister 1990, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF26FF029D64FB91FFD53478" author="Coad, B. W." box="[1305,1428,1122,1149]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" refId="ref270771" refString="Coad, B. W. (1995) Encyclopedia of Canadian Fishes. Canadian Museum of Nature and Canadian Sportfishing Productions Inc., Waterdown." type="book" year="1995">Coad 1995</bibRefCitation>
) and Russian scientists (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FF26FF029A7AFB75F96E34A4" author="Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Fedorov, V. V." box="[519,815,1159,1185]" pageId="183" pageNumber="184" pagination="7 - 69" refId="ref321798" refString="Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Fedorov, V. V. (2000) Chapter 1. Class Cephalaspidomorphi - Lampreys. Class Chondrichthyes - Cartilaginous fishes. Class Holocephali - Chimaeras. Class Osteichthyes - Bony fishes. In: Catalog of Vertebrates of Kamchatka and Adjacent Waters. Kamchatsky Pechatny Dvor, Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky, Russia, pp. 7 - 69 [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="2000">Sheiko and Fedorov 2000</bibRefCitation>
), as well as many 
<collectingCountry id="F3007650FF26FF029C7CFB75FE7234A4" box="[1025,1075,1159,1185]" name="United States of America" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">U.S.</collectingCountry>
scientists (e.g., Mecklenburg 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029DF5FB75FAA234C0" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">et al.</emphasis>
2002), call it the Polar Eelpout. With the specific epithet 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FF26FF029B0FFB59F98934C0" box="[882,968,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="183" pageNumber="184">polaris,</emphasis>
it is logical and less confusing to use the name Polar Eelpout.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
